benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account audit logs with history by account id

covered: Valid Request scenario (TC01) confirms retrieval of audit logs for a valid accountId.
Empty Response scenario (TC02) covers accounts with no audit logs.
Not Found/404 handling for non-existent account (TC03).
Input validation for accountId format (TC04, TC17).
Authorization handling with missing and invalid/expired tokens (TC05, TC06).
Server error handling (500) when the database is unavailable (TC07).
Query parameter handling, including ignoring unsupported parameters (TC08).
Security validation against SQL injection in accountId path (TC10).
Performance and scalability tests: large histories (TC09) and 100 concurrent requests (TC11).
Regression test covering missing audit log fields (TC12).
Integration test for degraded dependency service (TC13).
Edge cases covering whitespace in accountId (TC14), uppercase IDs (TC15), max UUID length IDs (TC16), and partial IDs (TC17).
gaps: Pagination handling for large result sets is not explicitly tested.
Rate limiting/throttling behavior is not tested.
Caching behavior and caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) are not tested.
403 Forbidden scenarios for insufficient privileges are not tested.
Explicit 204 responses or 304 Not Modified behavior is not covered.
Additional explicit schema validation across all items for all fields beyond TC12 could be strengthened.
recommendations: Add pagination tests for GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogsWithHistory using page and pageSize parameters to verify correct paging and boundaries.
Add a dedicated 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions beyond just 401/unauthorized.
Include caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and proper handling of 304 Not Modified if applicable.
Add rate limiting tests (e.g., throttle several requests in a short time and verify 429 responses).
Enhance edge-case coverage with more variations on accountId formats (e.g., multiple spaces, mixed casing) and verify consistent error behavior.
Consider a focused schema-validation test that asserts every AuditLog object conforms to the full schema across multiple pages/datasets.
